HEADWORD: Spurgall
<hw>Spur"gall`</hw> <pr>(-g⟦add⟧l`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A place
galled or excoriated by much using of the spur.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spurgall</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Spurgall
<hw>Spur"gall`</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To gall or wound with a
spur.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spurge</ent>⟦br⟧
